  schema:name "Oral Method, in partnership with Factory Theatre, presents: Vernal";
  schema:description """
	Join us for an evening of new writing, experimental writing! <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Alex Ateah<span><br/></span>Ariella Garmaise<span><br/></span>Knowah Holder<span><br/></span>Stephen Jackman-Torkoff<span><br/></span>Erum Khan<span><br/></span>Aliya Pabani<span><br/></span>feat. Simone Hogeveen and Wendi Jiang<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Organized by Kalale Dalton-Lutale and Esmé Hogeveen with support from the Toronto Arts Council<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Poster by Maddie Kingston<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Doors: 7PM<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Readings: 7:30PM<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Venue: Factory Theatre, 125 Bathurst St, Toronto<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Tickets are General Admission. A very limited amount of tickets will be available at the door on Friday, March 20. We recommend buying online to ensure you secure a ticket!</span><span><br/></span>
""";
